---
title: Animated Donut Chart
description: SVG donut chart animated with `stroke-dashoffset` — no JavaScript required.
slug: donut-chart
cssFile: donut-chart.css
explanation: "An SVG `<circle>` with `fill: none` and `stroke` becomes a ring. `stroke-dasharray` sets the dash length equal to the circle's circumference (`2πr`). `stroke-dashoffset` shifts the dash — at full offset (equal to circumference) the stroke is invisible; at 0 the full ring is drawn. Animating from full offset to the target value fills the arc. The percentage shown is `dashoffset = circumference × (1 - percentage)`. A `rotate(-90deg)` on the SVG starts drawing from the top."
---
{% extends "example.njk" %}
{% block demo %}
<div class="donuts">
	<div class="donut-wrap">
		<div class="donut-center" style="position:relative">
			<svg class="donut-svg" width="100" height="100" viewBox="0 0 80 80">
				<circle class="donut-track" cx="40" cy="40" r="35"/>
				<circle class="donut-fill donut-fill-green" cx="40" cy="40" r="35"/>
			</svg>
			<div class="donut-label-wrap">
				<span class="donut-pct" style="color:var(--accent)">75%</span>
			</div>
		</div>
		<span class="donut-name">CSS</span>
	</div>
	<div class="donut-wrap">
		<div class="donut-center" style="position:relative">
			<svg class="donut-svg" width="100" height="100" viewBox="0 0 80 80">
				<circle class="donut-track" cx="40" cy="40" r="35"/>
				<circle class="donut-fill donut-fill-sky" cx="40" cy="40" r="35"/>
			</svg>
			<div class="donut-label-wrap">
				<span class="donut-pct" style="color:var(--sky)">60%</span>
			</div>
		</div>
		<span class="donut-name">JS</span>
	</div>
	<div class="donut-wrap">
		<div class="donut-center" style="position:relative">
			<svg class="donut-svg" width="100" height="100" viewBox="0 0 80 80">
				<circle class="donut-track" cx="40" cy="40" r="35"/>
				<circle class="donut-fill donut-fill-coral" cx="40" cy="40" r="35"/>
			</svg>
			<div class="donut-label-wrap">
				<span class="donut-pct" style="color:var(--coral)">88%</span>
			</div>
		</div>
		<span class="donut-name">HTML</span>
	</div>
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block html_code %}
{%- highlight "html" %}
<svg width="100" height="100" viewBox="0 0 80 80"
     style="transform: rotate(-90deg)">
  <circle class="track" cx="40" cy="40" r="35"/>
  <circle class="fill"  cx="40" cy="40" r="35"/>
</svg>
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}

{% block css_code %}
{%- highlight "css" %}
.track {
  fill: none;
  stroke: var(--surface-2);
  stroke-width: 10;
}

.fill {
  fill: none;
  stroke: var(--accent);
  stroke-width: 10;
  stroke-linecap: round;
  /* circumference of r=35: 2π×35 ≈ 220 */
  stroke-dasharray: 220;
  /* offset = 220 × (1 - 0.75) = 55 for 75% */
  stroke-dashoffset: 55;
  animation: donut-draw 1.4s ease .2s both;
}

@keyframes donut-draw {
  from { stroke-dashoffset: 220; }
}
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}
